***********************************


For those using Linux, there is a script named "setup-python-linux.sh" which will
download various Python programming language related documentation to your computer.
It will require Subversion (SVN), Git and Hg (Mercurial) to be installed.


Links:

https://www.python.org/
http://learning-python.com/
http://www.dmoz.org/Computers/Programming/Languages/Python
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_%28programming_language%29
http://rosettacode.org/wiki/Python


